=====Usage notes=====
* This term can only be used when followed by a noun or noun phrase. It cannot be used as a standalone pronoun. Examples:
** '''Correct''':
**: {{ja-usex-inline|'''この'''[[色]]が好きです。|'''^この''' いろ が すき です。|I like '''this''' color.}}
*** A noun follows ''kono''.
** '''Incorrect''':
**: {{ja-usex-inline|'''この'''が好きです。|'''^この''' が すき です。|I like '''this''' ...}}
*** There must be a noun in place of the "...".
*** Using ''kono'' in this way is comparable to using English {{m|en|the}} without a noun after it (*''I like the.'').
* Almost always spelled in hiragana as {{lang|ja|この}}.

